    "Initially, the designers procured over 40,000 free, high-quality images from these sources.",
    "Subsequently, they meticulously evaluated each image, excluding those displaying incongruent decoration styles or unclear details.",
    "A stringent selection process was followed, and more than 20,000 images aligned with the established criteria.",
    "Furthermore, designers manually annotated the decoration styles and spatial functionalities depicted in these images.",
    "Ultimately, employing an open-source aesthetic evaluation mode 49, aesthetic scores were assigned to each image, culminating in the formation of ADSSFID-49."
